@GRMIDX{{index="Expressing Time" grammar="Expressing Time"}}

<body>

<h1>Expressing Time</h1>

@BGRNDSTART{{}}

@BGRND{{}}
<p>
To express a time the counter suffixes <a href="grammar-counter-ji.html">@KJ{{time}}<a> (o'clock)
and <a href="grammar-counter-bun.html">@KJ{{part}}<a> (minutes) are used.

<table class="sentence">
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@KJ{{noon^in*front}}4@KJ{{time}}desu.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      It's 4AM.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

@BGRND{{}}
<p>
To ask about the time or a time interval, @HI{{nan'}} is used with the above counter suffixes.

<table class="sentence">
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@KJ{{now^what^time}}desuka.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{7@KJ{{time}}10@KJ{{part}}desu.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      What time is it now?
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      It's 7:10.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

@BGRNDEND{{}}

